description:
Biography

Morena Baccarin, full name, Morena Silva de Vaz Setta Baccarin is a Brazilian, Italian, American actress, with various television, movie and voice acting work.

Acting Profile

Her first acting role was in the movie Perfume, eventually landing acting roles in high profile series, such as Firefly and Stargate SG-1.

Comic Related Movie Roles

Copycat

Morena Baccarin portrays the mutant Copycat also known as Vanessa Carlysle in 2016's Deadpool movie. In this movie, her character differs slightly than her traditional comic form, she is also the lead female protagonist.

Leslie Thompkins

Baccarin portrays Dr. Leslie Thompkins in the 2015 DC television show Gotham.

Black Canary (Voice acting)

Baccarin portrays the voice of Black Canary in the animated television series, Justice League Unlimited.

Talia al Ghul (Voice acting)

Baccarin has also voice acted the role of Talia al Ghul in various animated movies, including Son of Batman and Batman: Bad Blood.
name: Morena Baccarin

deck: Louis Bright-Raven is a professional editor, writer, and illustrator who has worked for Arrow Comics, Ronin Studios, HyattArt Comics, TSR / Wizards of the Coast, Steve Jackson Games, and numerous other comics, role-playing game, and genre fiction magazine publishers. He has also been a pop culture journalist since the mid 1980s.
name: Louis Bright-Raven
